> **Authoring rule (the anti-drift discipline):** every line below is either (a) an **address/link**,
> (b) a **one-line fact this project owns** (identity, phase, own edges), or (c) a **pointer that names
> the owning file**. A line that *restates a fact another file owns* is a defect — delete it, link instead.
> Anything evicted from this always-loaded file MUST land in a lower tier in the same change — eviction
> without a destination is a translation-ledger violation.

